name: Air Jordan 7 Retro Olympic 2004 release
description:
Size 13 
PRE OWNED 
Very Near deadstock
comes with original box and retro card.


One of the few commercially released Air Jordans to feature a number other than the iconic #23, these Olympic VII’s featured the number 9 on the back heel.  These kicks are the retroed versions of the exact sneakers MJ wore during the 1992 Olympics in Barcelona.  During these Olympics, Mike played on the legendary “Dream Team” which consisted of some of the greatest NBA players at the time and of all-time because this was the first time NBA players were allowed to play in the Olympics.  MJ took on the number 9 because of Olympic numbering rules.  The sneakers showcase silver and white leather uppers, while mostly the rest of the sneaker is accented in red and gold.  The tongue, ankle, and outsole are a navy blue color showing the sneaker’s American flag inspiration.

The Air Jordan 6 (VI) Retro – Black / Deep Infrared were released onAugust 23, 2000, and retailed for $120.ï¿½ They feature an all black suede upper with red accents, including around the clear sole and visible air sole unit, as well as the Jumpman logo and lace locks. The heel tab is huge, and features a hard design, as opposed to the soft loop that we see usually on shoes.ï¿½ The Air Jordan 6 (VI) features the lace locks and clear soles from the Air Jordan 5 (V), but besides that is a whole new shoe.

name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Concord
description:
Brand New Deadstock
will be shipped double boxed 



Remember the lines? Remember the unruly crowds? Remember the numerous news outlets covering the release? Remember the joy you had when you secured your pair? If you were one of the many outside of any retailer that happened to carry Jordan Brand product this time last year, you may have noticed increased security; possibly city police officers. Exactly one year ago today was one of the best, and possibly one of the worst days for the sneaker culture. The 2011 release of the Air Jordan 11 “Concord” was met with hoopla never seen before for a sneaker. Arguably the most popular shoe in the entire Air Jordan catalog, the “Concords” were a must have for any sneaker fan, and the release shined a light on some of the recent issues that have occurred regarding sneakers.

Nonetheless, the Air Jordan 11 “Concord” is one of the greatest shoes of all time. Proof the popularity has not waned was supported when the sneakers restocked randomly at Finish Line within the last month and sold out in minutes. Do you own a pair of “Concords”? Were you able to cop on the original release date? Let us know your story in the comments below, or on Twitter.

name: Air Jordan 21 Italian Red Suede
description:
Size 13 
*Pre Owned*
very good condition

This is the Air Jordan XXI (21) in the varsity red suede, metallic silver, and black color way. The upper is mostly varsity red suede with metallic silver and black accents around the shoe. D'Wayne Edwards designed this shoe using the Bentley Continental GT Coupe as inspiration. The Air Jordan XXI (21) continued Jordan Brand innovation with the idea of interchangeable pods giving the user the option to choose their style of play. This IPS (Independent Podular Suspension) concept may have seen weird back in 2006 but now Nike has incorporated in many different models such as the Kobe System and Air Jordan 2012. Most people take this model for granted and don't realize that it is part of the Air Jordan legacy that has led to the footwear present and future.
